Nobuo Arai ( ?) (1909  June 15, 1990) was a Japanese swimmer who competed at the 1928 Summer Olympics in Amsterdam where he won a silver medal in Men's 4x200m freestyle relay event. He was also fourth in the semifinal of 1500 m freestyle event and did not start in the semifinal of 400 m freestyle event and did not advance in both occasions.[clarification needed] 
